      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW KENNETH (8) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 22.77 when a 0.7 lengths winner over 400m at this track last time. Has a strong record from box 8, including two wins. The one to beat again. SICILY (2) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 7 lengths at this track in a handy 22.73 beating Radar's Patrol. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from five attempts. Significant danger. BONDED (6) was game in defeat off a low draw at the latest outing, finishing second and beaten 0.8 lengths (22.96) behind Snitch Adams at Warragul. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Will give a great sight again. ELITE HEAT (1) is right in the mix.",
